article.headline: Loyola of Chicago 69, Ill.-Chicago 60
article.story: CHICAGO -- Christian Thomas had 23 points and 11 rebounds on Saturday and Loyola of Chicago ended a four-game losing streak by beating Illinois-Chicago 69-60. Jordan Hicks added 18 points and Devon Turk scored 10 for the Ramblers (14-12, 4-9 Horizon), who never trailed in the contest. Marc Brown scored 13 points to lead the Flames (15-11, 6-7). Gary Talton and Hayden Humes had 10 points apiece for Illinois-Chicago. UIC won the previous meeting, 61-59 at home on Jan. 16. Loyola led 36-23 at halftime, and the Ramblers' lead never got below four points in the second half. The Flames' last game was a triple-overtime 88-83 win at Youngstown State on Sunday.
